{"TopicId":179430,"ForumId":44,"TopicTitle":"ISS Discussion Thread","CreatedByName":"NSEP","CreatedById":165635,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-31T11:13:10Z","PageNum":10,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-20T04:53:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo, the perigees are currently concentrated at the ISS altitude,\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA chance to check the protective properties of the insulation.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"RCgothic","CreatedById":132560,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-20T13:30:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLEO Labs are now speculating effectively that the ASAT interceptor hit the target from behind at greater than orbital velocity, hence the bias of debris into higher apogees rather than lower perigees. This would mean it wasn\u0027t a hypervelocity collision, which has implications for the size and distribution of the pieces.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis would be unusual for interceptors, which usually just get in the way of the target. This would mean the ASAT would need to be going at greater than orbital velocity, which seems like a lot of effort to go to for not much benefit to the interceptor. It needs a much larger launcher.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere are plusses and minuses. The pieces are likely to be a lot larger and fewer of them, which means we can track a lot more of them as a percentage. This makes avoidance manoeuvres more feasible.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOn the negative, the higher apogees and larger individual masses means the debris is likely to hang around for longer.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedOther\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed3175813781\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?app=core\u0026amp;module=system\u0026amp;controller=embed\u0026amp;url=https://twitter.com/LeoLabs_Space/status/1461766491305660429?s=20\u0022 style=\u0022height:556px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DDE","CreatedById":146349,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-21T15:31:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224057516\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179430\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221637415003\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022132560\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022RCgothic\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 11/20/2021 at 4:30 PM, RCgothic said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis would be unusual for interceptors, which usually just get in the way of the target. This would mean the ASAT would need to be going at greater than orbital velocity, which seems like a lot of effort to go to for not much benefit to the interceptor. It needs a much larger launcher.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt feels like they paid \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Delta-V\u0022\u003EdV\u003C/abbr\u003E to make it easier on the seeker. Not unusual: the Soviets fielded co-orbital ASAT long before they began DA-ASAT experiments.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SSTO Crasher","CreatedById":215483,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-23T00:16:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI feel extremely mad about the missile test for 2 main reasons.\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\n1. they could have almost killed the crew of the iss including cosmonauts THEIR OWN PEOPLE, just to advance their military\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n2. I am so sick I could puke with space agency\u2019s and military\u2019s using space as their military testing ground. I mean it\u2019s disgusting how they would bring their violence and war to a once peaceful frontier just to advance selfish military objectives and try to get ahead of their competition (The USA, my home country).\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\ni mean cmon, we have already fought a war in literally every place imaginable, let\u2019s not bring those wars to space\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JoeSchmuckatelli","CreatedById":154477,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-23T00:41:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224058335\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179430\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221637626569\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022215483\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022SSTO Crasher\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n23 minutes ago, \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Single Stage to Orbit\u0022\u003ESSTO\u003C/abbr\u003E Crasher said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nwe have already fought a war in literally every place imaginable, let\u2019s not bring those wars to space\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWelcome.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:8px;\u0022\u003E(this next is meant to be snarky / funny)\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u0026lt;Looks around at all the people and history of humanity...\u0026gt;\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou must be new here.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"cubinator","CreatedById":150330,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-23T01:08:50Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224058342\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179430\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221637628083\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022154477\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022JoeSchmuckatelli\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n28 minutes ago, JoeSchmuckatelli said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWelcome.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:8px;\u0022\u003E(this next is meant to be snarky / funny)\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u0026lt;Looks around at all the people and history of humanity...\u0026gt;\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou must be new here.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWe are all new here, and we can do better than this.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DDE","CreatedById":146349,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-23T07:38:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224058335\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179430\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221637626569\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022215483\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022SSTO Crasher\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n7 hours ago, \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Single Stage to Orbit\u0022\u003ESSTO\u003C/abbr\u003E Crasher said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nto a once peaceful frontier\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n*yawn*\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe military got there before everyone else did, and various ASAT tests have been going on since 1964. Space never was peaceful, and as soon as there would be a sufficient motivation to see an ASAT program from start to finish (e.g. ASM-135 was triggered by the Soviet US-A/MKRTs Legenda and the way it could make aircraft carriers vulnerable) it has happened.\u00A0\u003Cem\u003ERaison d\u0027etat\u003C/em\u003E, as always, trumps all.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sh1pman","CreatedById":147869,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-23T11:44:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224058426\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179430\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221637653123\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022146349\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022DDE\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, DDE said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n*yawn*\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe military got there before everyone else did, and various ASAT tests have been going on since 1964. Space never was peaceful, and as soon as there would be a sufficient motivation to see an ASAT program from start to finish (e.g. ASM-135 was triggered by the Soviet US-A/MKRTs Legenda and the way it could make aircraft carriers vulnerable) it has happened.\u00A0\u003Cem\u003ERaison d\u0027etat\u003C/em\u003E, as always, trumps all.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u2019s ok if countries do their military stuff there, but in a way that doesn\u2019t fill the orbit with deadly shrapnel that endangers everything, including people. (e.g. X-37B and Russian inspector satellites didn\u2019t generate nearly as much condemnation). Similarly, nuclear tests were banned because they produced fallout and raised the amount of radioactive isotopes like \u003Csup\u003E14\u003C/sup\u003EC in the atmosphere.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SSTO Crasher","CreatedById":215483,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-23T12:42:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224058342\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179430\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221637628083\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022154477\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022JoeSchmuckatelli\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n12 hours ago, JoeSchmuckatelli said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u0026lt;Looks around at all the people and history of humanity...\u0026gt;\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou must be new here.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\ntrust me I know about the other missile tests, and I was mad at those, but this one is different. It was 100% reckless to test that missile and put the crew of the iss in danger\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222021-11-23T12:46:38Z\u0022 title=\u002211/23/2021 12:46  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00222 yr\u0022\u003ENovember 23, 2021\u003C/time\u003E by SSTO Crasher\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DDE","CreatedById":146349,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-23T13:09:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224058485\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179430\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221637671362\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022215483\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022SSTO Crasher\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n26 minutes ago, \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Single Stage to Orbit\u0022\u003ESSTO\u003C/abbr\u003E Crasher said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nput the crew of the iss in danger\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot in the opinion of the people conducting the test. Therefore at most you\u0027re looking at negligence and willful blindness.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SSTO Crasher","CreatedById":215483,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-23T13:14:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224058426\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179430\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221637653123\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022146349\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022DDE\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 hours ago, DDE said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe military got there before everyone else did,\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOk this is technically wrong, the German v2 tests were the first thing to reach space BUT those tests were all failed and they did not intend to reach space on those tests. After that captured v2s were brought to America for testing during operation paper clip, which was funded by the USAF but those rockets were meant to be used for testing for future rockets.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JoeSchmuckatelli","CreatedById":154477,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-23T13:43:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224058491\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179430\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221637673264\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022215483\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022SSTO Crasher\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n24 minutes ago, \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Single Stage to Orbit\u0022\u003ESSTO\u003C/abbr\u003E Crasher said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nfunded by the USAF but those rockets were meant to be used for testing for future rockets\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes.\u00A0 Postwar USAF research was for purely peaceful and scientific purposes.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-23T14:19:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe very first flights of Vostok and Mercury are devoted to space reconnaissance and orbital intercepts (aiming the orbital targets and observing the ground objects).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nVostok was from the same family with photospysats and warhead.\u003Cbr\u003E\nMercury-Gemini-Apollo were steps to build the lunar outpost (first planned by the pure military Horizon Project, several years before the first space flight.).\u003Cbr\u003E\nGemini was a part of spy/recon (and partially combat, if implement the Commanche-like rocket consoles from some project) sat MOL.\u003Cbr\u003E\nVostok/Voskhod, Mercury, Gemini were launched by ICBM (Mercury and Gemini - by the real ICBM), V/V - by the cancelled ICBM.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFrom Terra with love.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWithout arm race there still would be no crewed program.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DDE","CreatedById":146349,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-23T14:32:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224058504\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179430\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221637677154\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129408\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kerbiloid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n13 minutes ago, kerbiloid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nVostok was from the same family with photospysats\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere\u0027s also the question of whether Gagarin had a Makarov under his seat.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-23T14:34:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224058509\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179430\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221637677940\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022146349\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022DDE\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 minutes ago, DDE said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere\u0027s also the question of whether Gagarin had a Makarov under his seat.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHow could he not have? Bears and so on. He was landing outside of the capsule, after all.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n8 shells - 8 bears. And a backup clip.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JoeSchmuckatelli","CreatedById":154477,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-23T14:54:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224058509\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179430\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221637677940\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022146349\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022DDE\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n18 minutes ago, DDE said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGagarin had a Makarov\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224058512\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179430\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221637678081\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129408\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kerbiloid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n16 minutes ago, kerbiloid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBears and so on...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n8 shells - 8 bears\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRussia must have small bears.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n...\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you ask an Alaskan what pistol to carry in case of Grizzlies, he would say, \u0027a .22\u0027\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n(which might surprise you)\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u0027why so small?\u0027 you might ask.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe answer?\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u0027So it won\u0027t hurt so much when the bear takes the pistol away from you and shoves it up your keester!\u0027\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SSTO Crasher","CreatedById":215483,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-23T15:00:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224058509\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179430\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221637677940\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022146349\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022DDE\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n28 minutes ago, DDE said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere\u0027s also the question of whether Gagarin had a Makarov under his seat\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThey have bears with AK\u2019s in the areas where they landed\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224058504\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179430\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221637677154\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129408\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kerbiloid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n42 minutes ago, kerbiloid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nVostok was from the same family with photospysats and warhead.\u003Cbr\u003E\nMercury-Gemini-Apollo were steps to build the lunar outpost (first planned by the pure military Horizon Project, several years before the first space flight.).\u003Cbr\u003E\nGemini was a part of spy/recon (and partially combat, if implement the Commanche-like rocket consoles from some project) sat MOL.\u003Cbr\u003E\nVostok/Voskhod, Mercury, Gemini were launched by ICBM (Mercury and Gemini - by the real ICBM), V/V - by the cancelled ICBM.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nVostok was funded by the military but used for peaceful reasons. Mercury-Gemini-Apollo existed for the sole reason of beating the Soviets, both salut 1 and Skylab very well could have been used for military purposes but were not. And the only reason ICBMs were used as the rockets were because those were the only rockets capable of doing so, and before the very first American launch attempt Kennedy ordered a new rocket be built (vanguard) to show that we would not use our weapons of war for space. But that rocket failed so he was forced to use an ICBM\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWe need to get back on topic though\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-23T15:08:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224058523\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179430\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221637679609\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022215483\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022SSTO Crasher\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n8 minutes ago, \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Single Stage to Orbit\u0022\u003ESSTO\u003C/abbr\u003E Crasher said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThey have bears with AK\u2019s in the areas where they landed\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhy arm a mount with rifles?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224058522\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179430\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221637679270\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022154477\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022JoeSchmuckatelli\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n16 minutes ago, JoeSchmuckatelli said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224058512\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179430\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221637678081\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129408\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kerbiloid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n36 minutes ago, kerbiloid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n8 shells - 8 bears\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRussia must have small bears.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe aim is not to kill a bear, but just remind him, who is alpha-predator on the planet.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JoeSchmuckatelli","CreatedById":154477,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-23T15:32:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224058525\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179430\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221637680102\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129408\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kerbiloid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n25 minutes ago, kerbiloid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhy arm a mount\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.pinterest.com/pin/245798092146141505/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://www.pinterest.com/pin/245798092146141505/\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-23T15:54:50Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224058534\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179430\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221637681574\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022154477\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022JoeSchmuckatelli\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n22 minutes ago, JoeSchmuckatelli said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.pinterest.com/pin/245798092146141505/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://www.pinterest.com/pin/245798092146141505/\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe classics\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022bear-cavalry.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002280.60\u0022 height=\u0022806\u0022 width=\u00221000\u0022 src=\u0022https://ru.mdz-moskau.eu/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/bear-cavalry.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E\nBut the mount isn\u0027t armed. The rider is.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"wumpus","CreatedById":133850,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-23T19:39:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224058538\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179430\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221637682890\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129408\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kerbiloid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, kerbiloid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe classics\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022#\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003C/a\u003E \u003Cspan\u003EHide contents\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E\nBut the mount isn\u0027t armed. The rider is.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u00221_swedish-moose-cavalry.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002281.80\u0022 height=\u0022517\u0022 width=\u0022632\u0022 src=\u0022https://listverse.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/1_swedish-moose-cavalry.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m not sure the lance is needed.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe link claims that they were indeed used, at least until Ivan the Terrible put a stop to in in Siberia.\u00A0 The early USSR was trying it again, but stopped when the Winter War needed real units.\u00A0 All I know is that backpackers in the US are told in no uncertain terms to never try to ride a moose (it is possible to get on when the moose is in a river, presumably swimming.\u00A0 Survival becomes impossible if you are still on when the moose regains its footing).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-23T19:56:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hiero%27s_Journey\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hiero\u0027s_Journey\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0is all about combat moose riding. though it\u0027s a fantasy.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nP.S.\u003Cbr\u003E\nI have a feeling that soon the zoocavalry will abandon this thread by the moderator efforts.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWe must urgently find out a way to link it to the ISS. Some kind of orbital zoo ISS module.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMaybe a moosewheel.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"FleshJeb","CreatedById":111640,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-23T20:08:58Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224058523\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179430\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221637679609\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022215483\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022SSTO Crasher\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Single Stage to Orbit\u0022\u003ESSTO\u003C/abbr\u003E Crasher said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThey have bears with AK\u2019s in the areas where they landed\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI knew a \u0022bear\u0022 that carried an M-14 in Vietnam.\u003Cbr\u003E\n(Dave was a Marine and a giant nerd. He would have loved KSP if he hadn\u0027t passed on before the release.)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBefore we all get sent to moderator-hell, here is the latest ISS news. Spacewalk set for Nov 30:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://blogs.nasa.gov/spacestation/2021/11/23/spacewalk-preps-during-human-research-robotics-and-physics-today/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://blogs.nasa.gov/spacestation/2021/11/23/spacewalk-preps-during-human-research-robotics-and-physics-today/\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SSTO Crasher","CreatedById":215483,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-23T20:24:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHow long has it been since the last spacewalk\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DDE","CreatedById":146349,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-24T05:27:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224058581\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179430\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221637696391\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022133850\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022wumpus\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n9 hours ago, wumpus said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe early USSR was trying it again, but stopped when the Winter War needed real units.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI distinctly remember an April Fools about that.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022max_g480_c12_r4x3_pd10\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002270.72\u0022 height=\u0022314\u0022 width=\u0022444\u0022 src=\u0022https://avatars.mds.yandex.net/get-turbo/3178886/rth9d9bab548d6fb6e8a428a63bf1d5f9ff/max_g480_c12_r4x3_pd10\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.popmech.ru/weapon/10162-rogataya-kavaleriya-boevye-losi/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://www.popmech.ru/weapon/10162-rogataya-kavaleriya-boevye-losi/\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224058586\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179430\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221637697373\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129408\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kerbiloid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n9 hours ago, kerbiloid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWe must urgently find out a way to link it to the ISS. Some kind of orbital zoo ISS module.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMaybe a moosewheel.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLooks like the Rusdian centrifuge project is tied to the inflatable module project, so no, definitely not relevant to the ISS.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://ria.ru/20170120/1486127952.html\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://ria.ru/20170120/1486127952.html\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}